org.apache.spark.storage

Class StorageLevel

  • Object
    • org.apache.spark.storage.StorageLevel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class StorageLevel
extends Object
implements java.io.Externalizable
    :: DeveloperApi :: Flags for controlling the storage of an RDD. Each StorageLevel records whether to use memory, or Tachyon, whether to drop the RDD to disk if it falls out of memory or Tachyon , whether to keep the data in memory in a serialized format, and whether to replicate the RDD partitions on multiple nodes.

    The StorageLevel$ singleton object contains some static constants for commonly useful storage levels. To create your own storage level object, use the factory method of the singleton object (StorageLevel(...)).
